Esso Research Experiences with Chemical Abstracts on Microfilm.AWeil, H.Emerson, W.G.Bolles, S.W.Lewenz, G.F. 
  Late in 1964, The Chemical Abstracts Service announcedthat in 1965 it would lease Chemical Abstracts in microfilmform to subscribers to its current printed abstracts.  Withthis move, microfilm entered a new stage - use in technical-information work as a publication medium for frequentlyemployed tools rather than for largely archival documents.